Sentencas: A thin film-based solid oxide fuel cell is deposited on a Ni-based metal porous support by pulsed laser deposition with a multi-scale-graded microstructure design.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell, around 1 mu m in thickness, is composed of a stabilized-zirconia/doped-ceria bi-layered dense electrolyte and nanostructured Ni-stabilized zirconia and La0.6Sr0.4CoO3 electrodes as the anode and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell is tested at intermediate temperatures (600-650 degrees C) with the aim to discern the degradation mechanisms occurring in the cell under accelerated conditions.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Under open circuit conditions, electrochemical performances are steady, indicating the stability of the cell.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Under electrical load, a progressive degradation is activated.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Post-test analysis reveals both mechanical and chemical degradation of the cell.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cracks and delamination of the thin films promote a significant nickel diffusion and new phase formation.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Signs of elemental distribution at low temperature are detected throughout the cell, indicating a combination of low energy surface elemental interdiffusion and electromigration effects.
Titulo: Effects of accelerated degradation on metal supported thin film-based solid oxide fuel cells
